properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 11 at 1:57AM CST until January 11 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI
properties.description:
...COMPLEX WINTER STORM WILL CONTINUE TO IMPACT THE REGION...

* WHAT...Mixed precipitation becoming freezing drizzle. Additional
snow accumulations of up to one tenth of an inch and ice
accumulations of a light glaze.

* WHERE...Lafayette County.

* WHEN...Until 6 AM CST early this morning.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Patchy blowing snow
could significantly reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM CST EARLY THIS MORNING... ...WINTER STORM WARNING IS CANCELLED
